{
  "texts": [
    "Bai et al. [54] find that LLMs still show significant stereotype biases when evaluated using two psychology-inspired measures, calling for the development of more robust value-aligned benchmarks.",
    "Other concerns relate to the reception of AIgenerated content.",
    "Jungherr and Rauchfleisch [57] found that AI-authored contribution to deliberative discussion were penalized by participants.",
    "Similarly, Yin et al. [58] found that AI-generated expressions of empathy increased perceived understanding, while this effect weakened when participants were informed that the messages were artificially generated.These five strengths point to a broader transformation in experimental design.",
    "LLMs shift stimuli from static, uniform treatments to dynamic, adaptive, and context-sensitive interventions."
  ]
}